<title>The 3/4 time signature. Dotted half note</title>
<!-- <tocimage>img108.png</tocimage> -->

<para>In this lesson a new rhythmic pattern is introduced:
One 8th note tied to group of one 8th and two 16th notes.
Note that this new pattern can be written in two different ways:</para>

<score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <music_border>0</music_border>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <music>
        (Metrica 2 4)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 c l g-)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(Barra Doble))
        (c (n a4 c)(n a4 n)(n a4 s g+)(n a4 s g-)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score>

<part>
<title>Lesson and note the differences</title>

<para>Lesson each measure and note how the new introduced pattern appears:</para>

<score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (Metrica 2 4)(n a4 n)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-) )
        (c (n a4 c g+)(n a4 c g-)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-) )
        (c (n a4 c g+)(n a4 c l g-)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score>

</part>

